I"%<p>In the latest GNOME update to GNOME 3.14, there is a different method required to move the window buttons in GNOME. This tutorial will outline an easy customization scheme.</p>

<hr />

<p>If not already installed, install gnome-tweak-tool</p>

<p>Open gnome-tweak-tool</p>

<p><code>gnome-tweak-tool</code></p>

<p>Click on Windows, and ensure that Maximize and Minimize are turned on.</p>

<p><img src="../../../img/linux/gnome_button_layout_01.png" alt="" /></p>

<p>Open dconf-editor using terminal or alt-F2</p>

<p><code>dconf-editor</code></p>

<p>Navigate to the following:</p>

<p><code>org.gnome.desktop.wm.preferences</code></p>

<p>Adjust the button-layout to read:</p>

<p><code>close,maximize,minimize</code></p>

<p><img src="../../../img/linux/gnome_button_layout_02.png" alt="" /></p>
:ET